Up 
post /Documents/Sync/{SynchronizeFromDate}/{Begin}/{Cap}
(syncDocuments)

Sync Documents

Process (since this is so complex):

  1. FOR EACH Document 1.1 Archive the Document 1.2 Merge in the Changes 1.5 After all Detail records are successfully stored, Update Document so Document.definition contains the serialized array of Details
  2. Get all Document records for this user that have changed since the sync date

Path parameters

SynchronizeFromDate (required)
Path Parameter — FROM date (descending) format: date-time
Begin (required)
Path Parameter — Beginning (skip) number of records (to page) format: int64
Cap (required)
Path Parameter — Maximum number of records to return format: int64

Consumes

  • application/json

Up 
post /Observations/Sync/{SynchronizeFromDate}/{Begin}/{Cap}
(syncObservations)

Sync Observations

Process (since this is so complex):

  1. FOR EACH OBSERVATION 1.1 Archive the Observation 1.2 Merge in the Changes 1.3 Translate the Observation Details 1.4 PERFORM SYNC MATCH AND UPDATE WHERE NECESSARY (TALK TO TRENT) 1.5 After all Detail records are successfully stored, Update Observation so Observation.definition contains the serialized array of Details
  2. Get all observation records for this user that have changed since the sync date

Path parameters

SynchronizeFromDate (required)
Path Parameter — format: date-time
Begin (required)
Path Parameter — Beginning (skip) number of records (to page) format: int64
Cap (required)
Path Parameter — Maximum number of records to return format: int64

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

204

No content

get /Report/Render/{IDDocument}/{Renderer}
(getRenderReport)

Request to render a report. To get rendered files, use getReportStageFile() Example HTML flow:

  1. Request /Report/Render/1247/default
  2. Extract GUIDReportDescription (i.e. "0x5984be9c8b000000") from response object.
  3. Open a new browser tab to: /Report/0x5984be9c8b000000/
  4. Rendered html page will subsequently request assets (images, css, etc)

Path parameters

IDDocument (required)
Path Parameter — ID of record format: int64
Renderer (required)
Path Parameter — Render format (default, html, pdf, json, etc)

Return type

ReportRenderResult

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "GUIDReportDescription" : "GUIDReportDescription"
}

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Object with report render UUID, or Error on failure ReportRenderResult

204

No content
